Question
Some class A has an addRequiredParam("pName","pDescr") defined inside its A::validParams().
My subclass B wants to make this pName an optional parameter and set some default value for it, but I dont see how, despite there must be a simple solution?
I tried
InputParameters
B::validParams()
{
  InputParameters params = A::validParams();
  params.makeParamNotRequired("pName");
  if(!params.isParamSetByUser("pName"))
    //* no such thing as setParam("pName", pValue) exists? So trying to add again:
    params.addParam("pName",newDefaultValue,"pDescr");
  return params;
}

but this doesn't take the newDefaultValue when i omit to define the pName in the input file. What am I missing out?
